The paper deals with a wireless network and its medium access algorithm, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI) and distributed computing (cs.DC). The algorithm also involves probability and local information, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency of the algorithm, which can be analyzed using mathematical optimization techniques (cs.MA).
